cs.DL, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CE

Reasoning: The paper examines the publication activities of pharmaceutical R&D laboratories, which involves analyzing large amounts of data and using computational methods. Therefore, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization, retrieval, and distribution of digital information. The paper also discusses the diversification of the disciplinary base towards computation, which suggests that cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely categories. Additionally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) are possible categories as the paper discusses the trend of Big Pharma becoming "network integrators" and relying on external research.
